Kevin Frac

About me

I am a geographer interested in topics related to climate, conservation and transportation. For my work with spatial data, I use as well as traditional GIS. In my masters thesis, I modelled where and when Lidar can effectively measure wind speed in Germany based on satellite observations of aerosols. I am currently seeking employment.

Projects Ive worked on

GeoAI in the Environmental Informatics lab of Uni Marburg

Project LiMeS (German only) at Fraunhofer IEE

The Mountain Exile Hypothesis in the Environmental Informatics lab of Uni Marburg

Education

M.Sc. in Physical Geography from Philipps University of Marburg

B.A. in History & German from UNC-Chapel Hill
